**MAC MINI AGENT SERVER**

**ADR-036 — GPU VRAM Allocation Policy**

**Status: DECIDED**

Date: April 4, 2026

Phase: 1  |  Setup Day Deliverable

Owner: Sheldon Wheeler

NIST Coverage:  SA-2 · SC-5 · SI-4 · SI-4(5) · AU-2 · AU-3

# **1.  Context and Decision**

Apple Silicon M1 Max applies a default Metal GPU memory cap of 75% of unified memory. On the 32GB configuration this limits GPU-addressable memory to 24,576 MB. On the 64GB configuration the default cap is 49,152 MB. For local LLM inference via Ollama this cap is the binding constraint on which model tiers can be loaded entirely in GPU memory.

The iogpu.wired_limit_mb sysctl kernel parameter allows the operator to raise this cap above the 75% default without disabling System Integrity Protection (SIP). The parameter resets to 0 (system default) on reboot unless re-applied by a LaunchDaemon at startup. The /etc/sysctl.conf persistence method requires SIP to be disabled and is rejected on security grounds.

Decision: Raise the GPU memory allocation above the 75% default using iogpu.wired_limit_mb, persisted via a LaunchDaemon plist at /Library/LaunchDaemons/com.openclaw.iogpu.wired_limit.plist. SIP remains intact. The exact MB value is determined on setup day by the hardware configuration purchased. Two configurations are fully specified in this ADR; the operator selects the applicable values at setup time.

