| ADR-020 | macOS Account Structure. LaunchDaemon is written and loaded under admin account. openclaw account has no write access to /Library/LaunchDaemons/. |
| ADR-021 | LayerModel Authority. GPU allocation directly enables Tier 2 model loads (32B) without CPU fallback. This ADR is a prerequisite for reliable Tier 2 inference. |
| ADR-023 | Encryption Posture. SIP remains enabled — no change to encryption posture. FileVault continues to protect all data at rest. |
| ADR-027 | Middleware Interceptor. No change. Interceptor token budget and circuit breaker are unaffected by GPU allocation. |
| ADR-031 | Change Management. LaunchDaemon installation triggers an ADR-031 change log entry on setup day. Any future modification to the MB value requires a new entry. |
| ADR-032 | NIST Compliance. SA-2 MET extended; SC-5 and SI-4 improved by this ADR. |
| ADR-033 | Dashboard Metrics. mem_used_gb alert thresholds amended in Section 7. hardware_metrics.sql alert view must be updated on setup day. |
| ADR-034 | Hardware Telemetry Collector. hw_collector.py reads mem_used_gb and mem_swap_gb. Revised thresholds apply to alert view only — no change to collector logic. |

# **13.  Risk Assessment**

| **Risk** | **Likelihood** | **Mitigation** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| OS memory starvation (swap > 0) | Low — headless workload with no GUI applications | Swap > 0 triggers critical Telegram alert (ADR-033). Reversal procedure in Section 9 resets to 75% default immediately without reboot. |
| System instability on 32 GB config at 87.5% | Low-Medium — tighter OS reserve than 64 GB | Reboot resets to 75% default if LaunchDaemon is unloaded. Intermediate value (85%) available as fallback before full reversal. |
| macOS update changes iogpu.wired_limit_mb behavior | Low — parameter stable since Sonoma 14.x | LaunchDaemon log captures applied value on each boot. Any behavioral change detected at next boot verification. ADR-031 review triggered on OS major version update. |
| Setting silently fails to apply at boot | Very Low | Boot log verification (Step 6 of setup sequence) and sysctl read confirm active value. LaunchDaemon stderr log captures any failure. |

# **14.  Future Considerations**

- If a 64 GB configuration is purchased and proves stable at 90% over 30 days of operation, the operator may evaluate raising to 92-93% (up to 61,440 MB). Any change requires a new ADR-031 change log entry and a 48-hour observation period with swap monitoring before the LaunchDaemon is updated.

- Phase 2 compliance_monitor should include a boot-time verification check confirming iogpu.wired_limit_mb matches the value recorded in this ADR. A mismatch (e.g., after an OS update that resets the parameter) should generate a Telegram alert.

- MLX vs. Ollama (ADR-027 open question, deferred to Phase 2) may affect the optimal GPU allocation. MLX uses a different memory management model than llama.cpp Metal backend. Revisit this ADR when MLX evaluation is conducted.

*ADR-036 recorded April 4, 2026. Configuration-specific MB values selected on setup day. SIP intact throughout.*